<TABLE border=0 align=center width="80%" cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td valign=top colspan=5><table border=0 width="100%"><tr><td><font size="+1"><B><a name="2001">Roll-A-Ball</a></B> / IPD No. <a class="linkid"  href="machine.cgi?id=2001">2001</a> <I>/ May, 1931 / 1 Player</I></font><br>&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=top></td></tr></table></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=top align=right><b>Average Fun Rating: </b></td><td colspan=4 width="80%" align=left valign=top><font color=red>No ratings on file</font> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[ <a href="rate/login.pl?gid=2001" target="do_a_rating">Be first to rate this game!</a> ]
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Manufacturer: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline><span title="Click here to perform a search for all pinball games manufactured by 'Hercules Novelty'"><a href="search.pl?searchtype=advanced&amp;mfgid=149">Hercules Novelty Company, Incorporated, <font size="-1">of Chicago, Illinois, USA</font> (1931-1932)</a></span></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Date Of Manufacture: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>May, 1931</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Type: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Pure Mechanical (PM)&nbsp;<a href="showhelp.pl?item=type&amp;highlight=PM#PM" title="Show Type Classifications" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a></td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align="right" valign=baseline><b>Serial Number Database:</b></td><td colspan=4 align="left" valign=baseline><a href="redirect.pl?http://www.ipsnd.net/View.aspx?id=2001">View at <I>The Internet Pinball Serial Number Database</I> (IPSND.net)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size="-1"><I>(External site)</i></font></td></tr><tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Specialty: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Table Top/Counter Game&nbsp;<a href="glossary.php#Table_Top/Counter_Game" title="Explain this specialty" target="help"><img alt="[?]" style="cursor: help;" src="/graphic/question.gif" border=0></a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notable Features: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>5 balls for 1 cent or 10 balls for 5 cents. <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Cabinet">Cabinet</a> measures 19 inches long, 13 5/8 inches wide, 7 inches high in the front, and 9 inches high in the back (not including <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Marquee">marquee</a>, or 12 inches high in the back including marquee). The metal <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Marquee">marquee</a> itself measures 8 3/4 inches long and 3 1/4 inches high.</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" valign=baseline align=right><b>Notes: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>Game was produced in a Standard version, and also in a "Souvenir Coin" version which included a <a target="glossary" class="glossarylink" href="/glossary.php#Token">token</a> vender.</td></tr>
<tr><td nowrap width="20%" align=right valign=baseline><b>Photos in: </b></td><td colspan=4 align=left valign=baseline>
Automatic Age, May 1931, page 150<br>
Automatic Age, July 1931, page 114<br>
Coin Machine Journal, October 1931, page 34<br>
Automatic Age, December 1931, page 102<br>
Marketplace Pictorial History, Page 8, June 1980<br>
</td></tr>
